50|$|Services within Antarctica are {{provided}} by a mixture of fixed-wing aircraft and helicopters. Fixed-wing services {{are provided}} {{by a pair of}} CASA 212-400 aircraft, equipped with skis, that are also operated by Skytraders. These aircraft operate from Wilkins runway and from smaller <b>snow</b> <b>runways</b> at each of the three permanent stations, as well as any field locations which provide the necessary flat area of snow or ice. Helicopter services {{are provided by}} three Eurocopter AS 350 BA Squirrel helicopters, operated by Helicopter Resources.|$|R
