5000|$|The Ice Runway [...] is the {{principal}} runway for the US Antarctic Program during the summer Antarctic field season due to its proximity to McMurdo Station. The other two runways {{in the area are}} the <b>snow</b> <b>runway</b> at Williams Field (NZWD) and the compacted <b>snow</b> <b>runway</b> at Phoenix Airfield (NZFX), which replaced Pegasus Field (NZPG) in 2017.|$|E
